@startuml
!theme plain
skinparam packageStyle rectangle
skinparam actorStyle awesome
skinparam backgroundColor #FEFEFE

title SmartLocate SG - Compare Candidate Sites (UC-20)
footer Generated: February 20, 2026

skinparam usecase {
    BackgroundColor #E3F2FD
    BorderColor #1976D2
    ArrowColor #424242
    FontSize 12
}

skinparam actor {
    BackgroundColor #FFF3E0
    BorderColor #F57C00
    FontSize 11
}

skinparam note {
    BackgroundColor #FFFDE7
    BorderColor #F9A825
}

' Actors
actor "User\n(A01/A02/A03)" as USER #FFE0B2
actor "System\n(Backend)" as A04 #B3E5FC

note right of USER
  **Represents three user types:**
  • A01: Small Business Owner
  • A02: Franchise/MNC Expansion Team
  • A03: Commercial Agent

  All have identical use case access
end note

' System Boundary
rectangle "SmartLocate SG\nCompare (Location Scores)" {

    usecase "UC-17\nView Portfolio" as UC17
    usecase "UC-20\nCompare Candidate\nSites (max 3)" as UC20
    usecase "UC-21\nExport Comparison\nReport (PDF)" as UC21

    usecase "Validate\nSite Selection" as ValidateSelection <<internal>>
    usecase "Retrieve\nScore Data" as RetrieveScores <<internal>>
    usecase "Format\nComparison Table\n& Charts" as FormatOutput <<internal>>

}

' User initiates
USER --> UC17 : initiates
USER --> UC20 : initiates
USER --> UC21 : initiates

' Include relationships
UC20 ..> UC17 : <<include>>
UC20 ..> ValidateSelection : <<include>>
UC20 ..> RetrieveScores : <<include>>
UC20 ..> FormatOutput : <<include>>
UC21 ..> UC20 : <<include>>

' A04 participates
ValidateSelection -- A04 : validates
RetrieveScores -- A04 : fetches
FormatOutput -- A04 : formats

' Extend relationships
UC20 <.. UC21 : <<extend>>\nuser requests\nPDF export

note right of UC20
  **Actors:** A01/A02/A03 (initiating), A04 (participating)

  **Preconditions:**
  1. User is logged in
  2. At least 2 candidate sites saved
     under the selected Business Profile

  **Postconditions:**
  1. Side-by-side score table displayed
     for all four scoring dimensions
  2. Bar or radar chart rendered

  **Flow:**
  1. User opens Comparison dashboard
  2. A04 retrieves candidate site list
  3. User selects 2-3 sites
  4. A04 validates selection (max 3)
  5. A04 retrieves full scores for
     selected sites (all 4 dimensions)
  6. A04 formats comparison table
     per FR-SCD-002
  7. A04 generates chart data
     per FR-SCD-003

  **Dimensions compared:**
  • Demographic Match
  • Accessibility
  • Rental Pressure
  • Competition Density
end note

note bottom of ValidateSelection
  **AC.1 - Max 3 guard**
  Blocks 4th site selection.
  Shows: "Maximum 3 sites
  for comparison"

  **EX.1 - Missing score data**
  Flags affected site with
  data-unavailable warning
end note

note top of A04
  **System (Backend) - A04**
  Handles:
  • Portfolio data retrieval
  • Selection count validation
  • Score data aggregation
  • Chart data generation
end note

legend bottom right
  **Relationships:**
  Solid line  ->  User initiates use case
  Dashed ⋯>  <<include>>  mandatory dependency
  Dashed ⟨⋯  <<extend>>   optional extension
  Solid line  --  System participates

  **UC-20 Requirements:**
  FR-SCD-001: Select up to 3 sites
  FR-SCD-002: Display comparison table
  FR-SCD-003: Display comparison charts
endlegend
@enduml